      <div xmlns="" class="section">
         <a name="Throats">
            <h3>Throats</h3>
         </a>
      </div>
      <div xmlns="" class="item">
         <div style="padding: 1px; padding-left: 8px;" class="tested">
            <a name="Sage_Gargle">
               <h4>Sage Gargle</h4>
            </a>
            <div style="display: inline; text-align: right; width: 100%;">
					| <a href="#top">top</a>
            </div>
            <br/>
            <p class="comment">8/10 | 02/09/2002 | takes 5 mins, makes 1 cup</p>
         </div>
         <div class="contents">
            <table border="0" cellspacing="3px">
               <tbody>
				
                  <tr>
                     <td>a few Fresh Sage Leaves</td>
                  </tr>
				
                  <tr class="even">
                     <td>1 cup Boiling Water</td>
                  </tr>
				
                  <tr>
                     <td>a dash Cider Vinegar</td>
                  </tr>

			
               </tbody>
            </table>
            <p>
				Pour boiling water into a cup. Add sage leaves and leave to
				soak for 5 mins. Strain, leave to cool a little and add cider
				vinegar. Garlge with mixture for relief of sore throats.
			</p>
            <p class="icomment">
				You can use 1 tsp of dried sage instead of the fresh leaves, 
				but it's not quite so effective.
			</p>
         </div>
      </div>
